##DESCRIPTION
##  Evaluate a function q(h)=(f(3+h)-f(3))/ h  given a polynomial f(x)
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##KEYWORDS('functions', 'polynomials', 'definition of derivative')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

## Edited K. Lesh, Union College 9/5/05

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
   "PGstandard.pl",
   "PGunion.pl",                # Union College utilities
   "Parser.pl",
   "PGcourse.pl",               # Customization file for the course
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PROBLEM();

$a1 = random(2,5,1);
$b1 = random(2,5,1);
$c1 = random(2,5,1);
$g1 = 1;
$g2 = .1;
$g3 = .01;
$g4 = .001;
$d1 = random(1,3,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Let \(f(x)=${a1}x^2 + $b1 x + $c1  \) and let
\( \displaystyle g(h)=\frac { f($d1 +h)-f($d1 ) }{ h } \).
$PAR
Determine each of the following:
\{BeginList("OL",type=>"a")\}
$ITEM 
\( g($g1) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
    $ITEMSEP
$ITEM
\( g($g2) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
    $ITEMSEP
$ITEM
\( g($g3) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
    $ITEMSEP
$ITEM
\( g($g4) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{EndList()\}

You will notice that the values that you entered are getting closer
and closer to a number we'll call \( L \).  This number is called the
limit of \( g(h) \) as \( h \) approaches \( 0 \) and is also 
called the derivative of \( f(x) \) at the point when \( x = $d1\).
We will see more of this when we get to the definition of derivative.
$PAR
Enter the value of \( L \):  \{ ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$ans1 =$a1*(2*$d1+$g1) + $b1;
$ans2 =$a1*(2*$d1+$g2) + $b1;
$ans3 =$a1*(2*$d1+$g3) + $b1;
$ans4 =$a1*(2*$d1+$g4) + $b1;
$ans5 =$a1*2*$d1 + $b1;

ANS(Real($ans1)->cmp);
ANS(Real($ans2)->cmp);
ANS(Real($ans3)->cmp);
ANS(Real($ans4)->cmp);
ANS(Real($ans5)->cmp);

ENDDOCUMENT();

